President Jacob Zuma says a single law should be implemented once a pre-colonial audit of land ownership is conducted. PARLIAMENT - President Jacob Zuma says government is considering the redesign and establishment of the National Land Claims Commission as a Chapter 9 Institution.Addressing the opening of the National House of Traditional Leaders at Parliament today, Zuma has called for unified efforts to accelerate land expropriation.He adds required constitutional amendments would be undertaken to effect the process of land redistribution. President Zuma says a single law should be implemented once a pre-colonial audit of land ownership is conducted. He stresses this will speed up the implementation of land redistribution without compensation. There are too many laws dealing with land which causes confusion and delays. In Parliament this week, the ANC voted against an Economic Freedom Fighters motion to review constitutional provisions on land expropriation. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)